    <text id="volume_03">
        <body>
            <pb id="p03-47" n="47"/>
            <div1 id="BQ-03-3-0004">
                <div2>
                    <head>
                        <title type="main">
                            <hi rend="i">THE BLAKE-VARLEY SKETCHBOOK</hi>
                        </title>
                    </head>
                    <p>In the facsimile recently published by Heinemann’s a number of the pages have been
inadvertently bound the wrong way round (the <hi rend="u">order</hi> is correct). Blake and Varley used the
sketchbook both ways up so some of the oblong composition should in fact appear “upside-down”. Vertical
compositions, as a general rule, were done with the bottom of the drawing at the outside edge of the page.</p>
                    <pb id="p03-48" n="48"/>
                    <p>The pages concerned are 9-10, 19-20, 35-6, 63-6, 71-98, 107-10, and 131-2.</p>
                    <byline>
                        <docAuthor>Martin <name>Butlin</name>
                        </docAuthor>
                    </byline>
                </div2>
            </div1>
        </body>
